# GM2 superset pulley pairing

When designing **supersets or giant sets** that include **Gym Monster 2 cable** exercises, group moves that share the same **pulley anchor zone** and, when possible, the **same attachment** so the athlete only adjusts height or load—not anchors or clips.

## Anchor zones (GM2)

| Zone | Where | Typical moves |
|------|--------|----------------|
| **Low vertical bars** | ~levels 1–4 on left/right posts | Leg curls (straps) |
| **Mid vertical bars** | ~levels 4–6 | Seated rows, chest-supported rows, mid flies |
| **High vertical bars** | ~levels 7–9 | Lat pulldown, straight-arm pulldown, triceps, high-to-low chops |
| **Floor platform** | Low platform anchors | Bulgarian split squat (handle), lateral raise (low), sissy squat (cable), some leg curls, wood chops—**not** interchangeable with mid-bar rows |

## Attachments (prefer matching within a superset)

| Attachment | Typical paired moves |
|------------|----------------------|
| **Smart PowerGrip handles** (one or two) | Lateral raise, single-arm row, BSS handle, sissy squat handle, low curls |
| **Cable row bar** (straight bar on both clips) | Seated row, chest-supported row, wide row |
| **Tricep rope** | Triceps extension, face pull (if rope preferred), some crunches |
| **Ankle straps** | Leg curl, knee raise, kickbacks |
| **Barbell hooks + pad** (Smith / cable barbell mode) | Bench, OHP, RDL—not mixed with handle supersets on the same clip |

## Rules

1. **Prefer same zone in a superset** — e.g. floor-platform BSS → floor-platform lateral raise before moving to mid/high chest fly.
2. **Prefer same attachment in a superset** — e.g. both moves on **handles** at low pulleys, or both on the **cable row bar** at mid pulleys; avoid handle → row bar → rope in one giant set unless muscle pairing clearly requires it.
3. **Height-only changes are OK** — two high-pulley moves at different notches with the **same attachment** (face pull → lat pulldown, both rope or both bar) are faster than anchor or attachment swaps.
4. **Smith work is separate** — barbell-mode Smith sets do not share cable anchors; do not pair Smith + cable only for “convenience” if it breaks muscle pairing or weekly balance.
5. **Document setup in program notes** — when pairing across zones or attachments is intentional (e.g. leg + chest), say why and accept the extra setup.

## Example (Push A home gym)

- **H1–H2:** Bulgarian Split Squat (Cable) → Lateral Raise (Cable) — both **floor platform**, both **Smart PowerGrip handles** (same-side or bilateral as prescribed).
- **H3–H4:** Chest Fly (Cable) → Overhead Triceps Extension (Cable) — fly **mid pulleys + handles**, then **high pulley + rope** (intentional height + attachment change; chest → triceps pairing; see rule 5).
